1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
We're looking at verses 8 through 11 this evening.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:09,000
And this is the second of the seven letters that are sent to the churches in Asia.

3
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:13,000
And we find that this church is written to the church at Smyrna.

4
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,000
And we'll read the text of Scripture, dig into the message this evening,

5
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:19,000
beginning in verse number 8 of Revelation 2.

6
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:21,000
Notice the Bible says this,

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:24,000
And unto the angel of the church in Smyrna write,

8
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:29,000
These things saith the first and the last, which was dead and is alive.

9
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:32,000
Aren't you thankful that we serve a living Savior? Hallelujah.

10
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:34,000
It says in verse 9,

11
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,000
I know thy works in tribulation and poverty, but thou art rich.

12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:42,000
And I know the blasphemy of them which say they are Jews and are not,

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,000
but are the synagogue of Satan.

14
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,000
Fear none of those things which thou shalt suffer.

15
00:00:48,000 --> 00:00:53,000
Behold, the devil shall cast some of you into prison, that ye may be tried.

16
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,000
And ye shall have tribulation ten days.

17
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Be thou faithful unto death, and I will give thee a crown of life.

18
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:06,000
He that hath an ear, let him hear what the Spirit saith unto the churches.

19
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:11,000
He that overcometh shall not be hurt of the second death.

20
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,000
We read this letter, we are reminded as we think about the church in Smyrna

21
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:20,000
that this is a local church that was in existence during the first century.

22
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:25,000
We understand that as we, last time we looked at the church at Ephesus

23
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
in chapter 2 verses 1 down through verse number 7,

24
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:32,000
and we made note in that first message that there's much that we know

25
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,000
about the church that was at Ephesus.

26
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Not only do we have the record of the missionary journeys,

27
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:41,000
the time in which Paul spent in the city of Ephesus,

28
00:01:41,000 --> 00:01:44,000
the ministry that he was able to partake of,

29
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:48,000
we have the letter that's written to the church at Ephesus,

30
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:50,000
the letter of Ephesians.

31
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:53,000
And then we also have Timothy, who's the pastor at Ephesus

32
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:57,000
that God uses Paul to write 1 and 2 Timothy to.

33
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
So we know a lot about the church at Ephesus.

34
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
We know a lot of what was going on, and so on and so forth.

35
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:05,000
But when we come to the church at Smyrna,

36
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:08,000
just as the cases with many of the other churches that we'll study here

37
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,000
on Sunday evenings over the next several weeks,

38
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:13,000
we do not know quite as much about these churches

39
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
as we did about the church in Ephesus.

40
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:19,000
However, we find that God gives us information here

41
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:23,000
with regard to this church and the work that was being done.

42
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,000
There are some things that we know about the city.

43
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:31,000
History would tell us that Smyrna was an extremely wicked city.

44
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:35,000
It was a city that was a seaport city that was located

45
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:40,000
roughly 35 miles north, kind of northwest of Ephesus.

46
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:44,000
And we find that they had lots of activity going on there

47
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:46,000
as it being a seaport city.

48
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
They were known for their emperor worship.

49
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
In fact, they had a place that was built there

50
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:55,000
specifically for emperor worship,

51
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,000
and of course being closely associated and allied with Rome

52
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
and all that was taking place there.

53
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,000
And so we know that this city,

54
00:03:02,000 --> 00:03:05,000
they were not only an extremely wicked city,

55
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:07,000
one in which were engaged in emperor worship,

56
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,000
but we understand that they were greatly opposed

57
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,000
to biblical Christianity.

58
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:15,000
And by the way, that's nothing new for any church

59
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:17,000
that's ever been planted in any place.

60
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:21,000
We find that the enemy is always in opposition

61
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:23,000
to what God is seeking to do.

62
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,000
If you're looking at a map today,

63
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:27,000
the city of Smyrna would be really where

64
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Izmir, Turkey is located today.

65
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,000
That's where you would find to just be able to kind of

66
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,000
in your mind have an idea of the location

67
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:38,000
of this ancient city, Smyrna, that is being written to.

68
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:40,000
As we look at this passage of scripture,

69
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,000
it's encouraging to me,

70
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:44,000
I mentioned this a couple of weeks ago,

71
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:46,000
that in each of the letters,

72
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
these seven letters that are being written,

73
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
that God says, I know thy works.

74
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
And we find that there's various aspects

75
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,000
in which God highlights about the works of the church,

76
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,000
but he also says to each of them in each of the letters,

77
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:03,000
he that hath an ear,

78
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:07,000
let him hear what the spirit saith unto the churches.

79
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:11,000
The best I can tell is you read in chapter number one,

80
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,000
maybe on the same page for you,

81
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,000
but in verse number 11, notice what the Bible says.

82
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:19,000
I am Alpha and Omega, the first and the last,

83
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:22,000
and what thou seest, write in a book.

84
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,000
Is that what your Bible says?

85
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:28,000
It says write in a book and send it, send what?

86
00:04:28,000 --> 00:04:30,000
The book that he's going to write

87
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:34,000
unto the seven churches which are in Asia.

88
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
So it's potentially the case

89
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,000
that all of these letters are contained

90
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:41,000
in one volume that would be sent.

91
00:04:41,000 --> 00:04:45,000
And we find that he says, as he concludes each of them,

92
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:47,000
and he lists out the churches there

93
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,000
in verse number 11 of chapter one,

94
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,000
but he says, let him, he that hath an ear,

95
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:53,000
let him hear what the spirit saith,

96
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,000
notice unto the churches, plural.

97
00:04:56,000 --> 00:04:59,000
And so this letter is addressed to,

98
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:01,000
according to verse number eight,

99
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:04,000
to the angel of the church, singular, that's in Smyrna.

100
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,000
It was the local church in Smyrna,

101
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:08,000
and the description, the details

102
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:10,000
that are contained within the letter

103
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:14,000
are applicable specifically to that local church.

104
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:17,000
But then he ends by saying, he that hath an ear,

105
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:19,000
let him hear what the spirit saith,

106
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:22,000
unto the churches, plural,

107
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:24,000
because there are seven churches

108
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:27,000
that are addressed in Revelation two and three.

109
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:30,000
And the reality is that we understand this evening

110
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:34,000
that the truth that is given to each of these churches

111
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:37,000
is appropriate and applicable for every believer

112
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,000
to be aware of and to have knowledge of.

113
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:42,000
And the reality, as I said a couple of weeks ago,

114
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,000
is that if these things were true

115
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:46,000
of the churches in the first century,

116
00:05:46,000 --> 00:05:51,000
then we must, we must take heed to what God gives,

117
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:53,000
and we must examine ourselves and say,

118
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,000
what is it within these letters,

119
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,000
if God were to write a letter to us,

120
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:01,000
if he were to evaluate our church,

121
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,000
Fellowship Baptist Church this evening,

122
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:04,000
what is it that he would say?

123
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:08,000
What parts of these letters would be included

124
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:10,000
in the letter that he would write to us?

125
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:12,000
If we look at the church at Smyrna,

126
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:15,000
as best we can tell, there's no correction that is given.

127
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,000
Now, there are some that argue

128
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:20,000
that in verse number nine, there's a correction given,

129
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,000
but I want you to see that there's no place

130
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:25,000
that God says to them to repent.

131
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
In the other letters, we find that as God points out

132
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:30,000
the error, the correction that he gives

133
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:33,000
to the particular churches, he follows that up

134
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:37,000
with a remedy, if you will, of repent and change your behavior

135
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,000
because what you're doing is not right.

136
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:41,000
Therefore, I don't really believe that verse number nine

137
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:45,000
is carrying with it a correction for the church specifically.

138
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:47,000
When he talks about, I know the blasphemy of them

139
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,000
which say they are Jews and are not,

140
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,000
but are the synagogue of Satan,

141
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,000
I don't think those are people

142
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,000
that are part of the church at Smyrna.

143
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:56,000
Those are people that are in the city of Smyrna,

144
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,000
but not part of the church at Smyrna

145
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:02,000
and that would lead us to say that this church,

146
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:04,000
we find that as we read these verses,

147
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:07,000
that God knows their works, but there's no correction given.

148
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:09,000
Now, let me be quick to say this,

149
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:12,000
it doesn't mean it's a perfect church.

150
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:13,000
Why do we know that?

151
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,000
Well, we know that because there are no perfect churches.

152
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:19,000
I'm thankful that the church, that the head of the church

153
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:22,000
is the Lord Jesus Christ and he is perfect.

154
00:07:22,000 --> 00:07:25,000
I'm thankful that he gave us a book that is perfect,

155
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:30,000
but we are imperfect people that make up churches

156
00:07:30,000 --> 00:07:32,000
and we find that Jesus said,

157
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:34,000
I will build my church and the gates of hell

158
00:07:34,000 --> 00:07:36,000
shall not prevail against it.

159
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:39,000
And as we follow his pattern, as we follow his truth,

160
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,000
that he allows us to accomplish

161
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
what he sets out for us to accomplish

162
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:47,000
and we find that the church in Smyrna is here addressed.

163
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,000
I want you to consider a few thoughts

164
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,000
with regard to this letter

165
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:55,000
and what it reveals to us about our savior.

166
00:07:55,000 --> 00:07:58,000
By the way, I'm so thankful for Jesus, aren't you?

167
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:03,000
We sing the song, Jesus is the sweetest name I know.

168
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:06,000
And truly that is the case this evening.

169
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:09,000
I hope that this evening, if you are in the presence

170
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,000
and you hear and we live in the world,

171
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:13,000
though we're not of the world,

172
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:15,000
there are times in which you hear individuals

173
00:08:16,000 --> 00:08:19,000
that will take the name of our savior in vain.

174
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:22,000
And oh, how that ought to grieve our hearts, why?

175
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,000
Because that's my savior, that's my God.

176
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,000
That's the one who died for me.

177
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:30,000
That's the one who is the altogether lovely one.

178
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:33,000
And we understand tonight that he indeed

179
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:35,000
is a wonderful savior.

180
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:39,000
Another song that we sing, he's a wonderful savior to me.

181
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,000
And I believe that this letter reveals to us

182
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:44,000
three aspects of our savior

183
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:46,000
that are worth our consideration this evening.

184
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:49,000
Notice with me number one, our conquering savior.

185
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,000
Notice in verse number eight,

186
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:52,000
as he begins writing to the church,

187
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,000
and he does this in each of the letters,

188
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:57,000
we find that he highlights some particular aspect

189
00:08:57,000 --> 00:09:00,000
or attribute that had been previously given

190
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:04,000
in chapter number one with regard to his person,

191
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,000
who he is.

192
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:09,000
He does not record and restate everything

193
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,000
that he says in the first chapter,

194
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:12,000
but for each of the churches,

195
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,000
there's a particular aspect of the nature

196
00:09:14,000 --> 00:09:18,000
and character of God that is highlighted.

197
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,000
Here in verse number eight,

198
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:22,000
the Bible says unto the angel of the church in Smyrna,

199
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:26,000
write, these things saith the first and the last,

200
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:29,000
which was dead and is alive.

201
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:31,000
We notice how Christ identifies himself

202
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:35,000
here to these believers that were facing difficulty.

203
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,000
These that were serving faithfully in Smyrna,

204
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,000
these that were dealing with opposition

205
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:43,000
with those that opposed Christianity,

206
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,000
and we find that Jesus,

207
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:48,000
as he begins to address this church,

208
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:51,000
he reminds them of two very important truths

209
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,000
that reveal to us and remind us

210
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:56,000
of the fact that our God is a conquering God,

211
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:58,000
and number one is that he is eternal.

212
00:09:58,000 --> 00:09:59,000
He says to them,

213
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,299
These things saith the first and the last.

214
00:10:02,299 --> 00:10:04,300
Aren't you thankful that our God has no beginning

215
00:10:04,300 --> 00:10:05,340
and no ending?

216
00:10:05,340 --> 00:10:07,979
That he indeed is Alpha and Omega.

217
00:10:07,979 --> 00:10:09,460
He is outside of time.

218
00:10:09,460 --> 00:10:11,140
He is always relevant.

219
00:10:11,140 --> 00:10:13,779
We find that he has given to us a book

220
00:10:13,779 --> 00:10:17,379
and he has provided to us with truth that endures,

221
00:10:17,379 --> 00:10:20,420
truth that is applicable and necessary

222
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:23,420
for every generation of humankind.

223
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:24,260
Why?

224
00:10:24,260 --> 00:10:26,500
Because our God is eternal.

225
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:29,139
And we understand the encouragement,

226
00:10:29,139 --> 00:10:30,500
the significance of this,

227
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:32,900
even as we think about the incarnation

228
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:34,180
during this time of year.

229
00:10:34,180 --> 00:10:36,380
And we think about the birth of our savior

230
00:10:36,380 --> 00:10:39,279
and how he left the throne room of heaven.

231
00:10:39,279 --> 00:10:41,819
And he never ceased to be God,

232
00:10:41,819 --> 00:10:44,299
but he took upon himself the form of a servant.

233
00:10:44,299 --> 00:10:45,139
Why?

234
00:10:45,139 --> 00:10:46,939
So that he could die for us.

235
00:10:46,939 --> 00:10:50,340
We find here this evening that not only does he remind

236
00:10:50,340 --> 00:10:53,979
these believers in Smyrna that he is eternal,

237
00:10:53,979 --> 00:10:57,459
but he also reminds them that he conquered death.

238
00:10:57,459 --> 00:11:01,139
He says this, which was dead and is alive.

239
00:11:01,139 --> 00:11:03,699
You'll remember that in chapter one in verse 18,

240
00:11:03,699 --> 00:11:06,180
he says, I am he that liveth and was dead.

241
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:08,260
And behold, I am alive forevermore.

242
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:09,099
Amen.

243
00:11:09,099 --> 00:11:12,980
And have the keys of hell and of death.

244
00:11:12,980 --> 00:11:16,739
What a joy to know that our savior conquered sin,

245
00:11:16,739 --> 00:11:18,139
death and the grave.

246
00:11:18,139 --> 00:11:20,220
That he rose triumphant.

247
00:11:20,220 --> 00:11:22,620
He conquered the enemy.

248
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:24,379
He conquered death.

249
00:11:24,379 --> 00:11:25,660
And what a joy that is.

250
00:11:25,660 --> 00:11:27,379
These believers that are being written to,

251
00:11:27,379 --> 00:11:29,500
remember as we studied the first chapter,

252
00:11:29,500 --> 00:11:31,900
we began to understand some of the difficulty

253
00:11:31,900 --> 00:11:33,819
that these believers were facing

254
00:11:33,819 --> 00:11:35,760
and all that they were dealing with,

255
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:39,500
with regard to the oppression and opposition,

256
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:43,059
that the Lord is seeking to encourage them.

257
00:11:43,059 --> 00:11:45,839
